1
00:00:11,800 --> 00:00:12,880
You?

2
00:00:14,040 --> 00:00:16,040
If all you wanted was rank and fortune,

3
00:00:16,112 --> 00:00:17,920
you wouldn't have defied
the commissioner.

4
00:00:20,320 --> 00:00:21,480
Then what am I doing it for?

5
00:00:27,960 --> 00:00:29,760
That's exactly what I'm curious about.

6
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:35,820
=Cases Between Us=

7
00:00:35,980 --> 00:00:38,940
=Episode 14=

8
00:00:50,280 --> 00:00:51,720
I thought

9
00:00:52,520 --> 00:00:54,240
after everything we'd been through,

10
00:00:55,120 --> 00:00:56,080
we were friends.

11
00:00:56,864 --> 00:00:58,080
Guess I got ahead of myself.

12
00:00:59,400 --> 00:01:01,120
Xie Qing was right.

13
00:01:01,520 --> 00:01:02,680
You're impossible

14
00:01:04,240 --> 00:01:04,880
to get close to.

15
00:01:06,240 --> 00:01:07,360
Looks like

16
00:01:07,880 --> 00:01:09,560
she's the only one
who knows your secret.

17
00:01:11,680 --> 00:01:12,800
What secret?

18
00:01:12,800 --> 00:01:14,040
She wouldn't tell me.

19
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:17,120
You should've seen her.

20
00:01:17,120 --> 00:01:18,120
She was so smug.

21
00:01:18,800 --> 00:01:19,920
She gave me a hit.

22
00:01:20,320 --> 00:01:21,040
Drink.

23
00:01:21,280 --> 00:01:22,640
She said to get you drunk.

24
00:01:22,640 --> 00:01:23,880
If you tell me,

25
00:01:23,904 --> 00:01:25,320
I'll know you see me as a friend.

26
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:38,880
You really want to know?

27
00:01:38,880 --> 00:01:39,880
I do.

28
00:01:44,240 --> 00:01:47,000
When I get drunk, I can't stop laughing.

29
00:01:47,840 --> 00:01:48,720
I can't control myself.

30
00:01:53,480 --> 00:01:54,840
When I first got to Britain,

31
00:01:55,000 --> 00:01:56,840
the locals used to bully the Chinese.

32
00:01:56,840 --> 00:01:57,800
One holiday,

33
00:01:57,800 --> 00:01:59,080
Xie Qing and I went out drinking.

34
00:01:59,080 --> 00:01:59,920
We got wasted.

35
00:02:00,880 --> 00:02:02,240
I just kept laughing.

36
00:02:02,240 --> 00:02:03,840
Someone at the next table

37
00:02:03,960 --> 00:02:05,280
thought I was laughing at them,

38
00:02:05,344 --> 00:02:06,640
so they came looking for trouble.

39
00:02:07,120 --> 00:02:08,320
Guess what happened?

40
00:02:08,760 --> 00:02:10,600
Xie Qing and I teamed up

41
00:02:11,080 --> 00:02:12,760
and gave them a taste

42
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,880
of Chinese drunken boxing.

43
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:18,080
Xie Qing then told me

44
00:02:18,280 --> 00:02:19,680
that in all the years she'd known me,

45
00:02:20,080 --> 00:02:22,240
I'd never smiled as much
as I did that night.

46
00:02:23,720 --> 00:02:25,120
That's your big secret?

47
00:02:30,640 --> 00:02:31,600
Not really.

48
00:02:32,320 --> 00:02:35,440
Tell me a real secret.

49
00:02:37,960 --> 00:02:40,000
I've noticed
that whenever you're emotional,

50
00:02:40,440 --> 00:02:41,280
angry,

51
00:02:42,320 --> 00:02:43,120
or anxious,

52
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:44,640
you eat candy.

53
00:02:46,720 --> 00:02:47,520
Why?

54
00:02:55,648 --> 00:02:57,200
Forget it if you don't want to say.

55
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:05,280
I'm an illegitimate son.

56
00:03:12,440 --> 00:03:14,000
Years ago, my grandfather

57
00:03:14,320 --> 00:03:16,000
supported the revolution.

58
00:03:17,080 --> 00:03:20,400
The men in the family were all executed,

59
00:03:20,400 --> 00:03:22,320
and the women were sold
into the Eight Alleys.

60
00:03:23,040 --> 00:03:23,720
My father met

61
00:03:23,720 --> 00:03:25,120
my mother there.

62
00:03:25,840 --> 00:03:27,400
Later, he bought her freedom

63
00:03:27,408 --> 00:03:28,880
and kept her in a separate house.

64
00:03:29,440 --> 00:03:30,720
Then I was born.

65
00:03:31,600 --> 00:03:33,520
I hardly ever saw my father.

66
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,800
Only on the Chinese New Year's Day

67
00:03:37,376 --> 00:03:39,160
was I allowed back to the family estate.

68
00:03:42,880 --> 00:03:44,384
Young masters and young mistresses,

69
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:45,880
let's hang the lanterns.

70
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:46,200
Come on.

71
00:03:46,200 --> 00:03:47,480
This is yours, Young Master.

72
00:03:47,480 --> 00:03:48,160
Hurry up.

73
00:03:48,880 --> 00:03:49,840
So beautiful.

74
00:03:49,840 --> 00:03:52,120
Madam's treating everyone to tanghulu.
[*Candied hawthorn]

75
00:03:52,520 --> 00:03:53,680
Tanghulu!

76
00:03:53,680 --> 00:03:54,960
- I want one.
- Here's yours.

77
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:55,620
I want one, too.

78
00:03:56,280 --> 00:03:56,960
Me too.

79
00:03:57,200 --> 00:03:58,300
- Thank you.
- Give me one.

80
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:58,630
Sure.

81
00:03:58,736 --> 00:03:59,870
- Thank you.
- Give me one.

82
00:03:59,960 --> 00:04:00,990
Easy.

83
00:04:02,240 --> 00:04:03,240
Do you want one?

84
00:04:05,760 --> 00:04:07,040
Here you go.

85
00:04:12,520 --> 00:04:14,720
In your dreams.

86
00:04:15,280 --> 00:04:16,600
Come over here.

87
00:04:17,000 --> 00:04:19,600
He says he wants tanghulu.

88
00:04:19,880 --> 00:04:22,440
A spawn from a brothel

89
00:04:22,760 --> 00:04:24,400
actually thinks he deserves one?

90
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:25,200
- Spawn!
- Spawn!

91
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,936
- Spawn!
- You're nothing but a spawn.

92
00:04:27,952 --> 00:04:29,200
- You deserve nothing.
- Spawn.

93
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,320
- You're pathetic!
- Spawn!

94
00:04:34,440 --> 00:04:36,080
Madam Yuan failed to discipline her son.

95
00:04:36,080 --> 00:04:37,760
Master ordered her to kneel until dawn.

96
00:04:38,520 --> 00:04:39,920
Mother. I was wrong.

97
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:41,880
I was wrong.

98
00:04:41,880 --> 00:04:43,280
Please spare my mother.

99
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:44,400
Hong.

100
00:04:44,400 --> 00:04:45,760
Hong, get up.

101
00:04:46,280 --> 00:04:47,320
It's the Master's order.

102
00:04:47,320 --> 00:04:48,880
Don't blame me for being heartless.

103
00:04:48,880 --> 00:04:50,680
Don't hit my mother.

104
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,560
Get away from me.

105
00:04:51,560 --> 00:04:53,720
Don't hit my mother.

106
00:04:53,720 --> 00:04:55,400
I like this.

107
00:04:55,760 --> 00:05:00,160
I like this.

108
00:05:00,600 --> 00:05:08,160
I like this.

109
00:05:26,480 --> 00:05:27,400
Since then,

110
00:05:27,680 --> 00:05:28,880
malt candy's been my favorite.

111
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,920
Now you know my secret.

112
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,400
Those two

113
00:05:55,400 --> 00:05:56,640
still aren't home?

114
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,120
Gone on a date?

115
00:05:59,880 --> 00:06:00,880
Those two?

116
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,920
One's glued to the police department,

117
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:04,360
the other to the newsroom.

118
00:06:05,040 --> 00:06:05,840
You're to blame.

119
00:06:06,240 --> 00:06:08,280
You always say
they never do anything worthwhile.

120
00:06:08,304 --> 00:06:09,632
Well, now they're hardly ever home.

121
00:06:10,320 --> 00:06:11,520
It's good they're not home.

122
00:06:11,520 --> 00:06:13,560
They drive me crazy
when they're around all day.

123
00:06:15,720 --> 00:06:17,640
Xinming Theater premiered a new show,

124
00:06:17,640 --> 00:06:18,560
The Emperor's Romance.

125
00:06:18,560 --> 00:06:19,600
(The Emperor's Romance)

126
00:06:19,600 --> 00:06:20,440
A private box.

127
00:06:20,512 --> 00:06:22,000
You can do whatever you want in there.

128
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,240
Get out!

129
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,400
Do whatever you like.

130
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:34,080
No wonder you were acting strange
on the last case.

131
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:38,120
So your dad is...

132
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:39,880
A warlord.

133
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:42,760
A warlord surnamed Yuan?

134
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:45,240
I took my mother's surname.

135
00:06:46,920 --> 00:06:48,800
He wouldn't let me take his.

136
00:06:50,840 --> 00:06:52,520
But after I got
into the military academy,

137
00:06:52,520 --> 00:06:53,840
he wanted me to change it.

138
00:06:55,120 --> 00:06:55,960
I refused.

139
00:06:56,600 --> 00:06:59,520
What does your mother do now?

140
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,360
She passed away.

141
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:10,720
I found out

142
00:07:10,720 --> 00:07:12,144
just before graduating from Britain.

143
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,120
I rushed home,

144
00:07:15,000 --> 00:07:16,200
but she's been buried.

145
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,720
I checked with the police department.

146
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:21,840
There was no death report

147
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,360
or death certificate.

148
00:07:25,960 --> 00:07:28,160
So I went looking for the body.

149
00:07:28,600 --> 00:07:30,080
I wanted to exhume it.

150
00:07:30,600 --> 00:07:32,480
Turns out the tomb was empty.

151
00:07:34,320 --> 00:07:35,040
That's why

152
00:07:35,040 --> 00:07:36,680
I resigned from the military

153
00:07:36,680 --> 00:07:37,880
and joined the police.

154
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:41,520
I want to find out how my mother died

155
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:43,960
so her soul can rest in peace.

156
00:07:45,160 --> 00:07:46,120
It's fine.

157
00:07:46,880 --> 00:07:48,480
The house is still here.

158
00:07:49,320 --> 00:07:52,840
I'll have Zhao Cai search it
inch by inch.

159
00:07:53,040 --> 00:07:54,840
We'll find something.

160
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:56,920
You should stay out of this.

161
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,280
It's fine.

162
00:07:58,280 --> 00:07:59,280
Our last cases

163
00:07:59,280 --> 00:08:00,560
worked out pretty well.

164
00:08:04,480 --> 00:08:05,480
Where are you going?

165
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:17,440
After Director Zheng was arrested,

166
00:08:17,680 --> 00:08:19,320
this turned up at my house.

167
00:08:22,560 --> 00:08:23,480
A dud?

168
00:08:25,000 --> 00:08:27,120
Seriously?
These assassins are unreliable.

169
00:08:27,440 --> 00:08:29,160
Even their threats cut corners.

170
00:08:30,760 --> 00:08:31,760
Don't wade

171
00:08:32,280 --> 00:08:33,280
into this mess.

172
00:08:38,120 --> 00:08:40,120
Now I've got to say something.

173
00:08:40,840 --> 00:08:43,360
You know what I like most?

174
00:08:45,080 --> 00:08:45,760
Fun.

175
00:08:47,040 --> 00:08:49,920
The more dangerous, the better.

176
00:08:50,560 --> 00:08:51,680
Don't overthink it.

177
00:08:53,480 --> 00:08:54,640
Let me make myself clear.

178
00:08:55,680 --> 00:08:57,040
I'm not doing this for you.

179
00:08:57,960 --> 00:08:59,480
I just like

180
00:09:01,760 --> 00:09:02,800
having fun.

181
00:09:30,280 --> 00:09:31,040
Easy there.

182
00:09:31,040 --> 00:09:32,760
Don't blame me

183
00:09:33,040 --> 00:09:34,800
if you get drunk.

184
00:09:56,480 --> 00:09:57,600
Judging by your tolerance,

185
00:09:58,960 --> 00:10:00,800
those foreigners
can't hold their liquor either.

186
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:02,880
Have fun!

187
00:10:04,800 --> 00:10:05,680
Have fun!

188
00:10:32,040 --> 00:10:32,960
Han Zhenzhu,

189
00:10:33,400 --> 00:10:34,280
you're paying for this.

190
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:36,440
Me?

191
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:37,720
You stole my headline.

192
00:10:40,680 --> 00:10:41,800
Fine.

193
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,080
It's on me.

194
00:10:43,080 --> 00:10:44,320
Petty lady.

195
00:10:44,480 --> 00:10:46,040
Yes, I'm petty.

196
00:10:46,040 --> 00:10:47,720
Eat up, petty lady.

197
00:10:53,440 --> 00:10:55,400
The police shut down
the Handan Pleasure House.

198
00:10:55,680 --> 00:10:57,920
A few of the girls
found work at the textile mill.

199
00:10:58,240 --> 00:10:59,680
But some of them

200
00:10:59,840 --> 00:11:01,160
went back to the Eight Alleys.

201
00:11:01,760 --> 00:11:02,760
By choice?

202
00:11:03,240 --> 00:11:04,280
Yes

203
00:11:04,640 --> 00:11:05,720
and no.

204
00:11:06,160 --> 00:11:08,000
No one chooses to be humiliated

205
00:11:08,320 --> 00:11:09,600
or treated like a plaything.

206
00:11:11,160 --> 00:11:12,280
If they want to survive,

207
00:11:13,280 --> 00:11:15,240
they cling to the only life they know,

208
00:11:15,600 --> 00:11:18,200
even if it's a swamp.

209
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:21,880
The swamp is already a part of them.

210
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:23,440
If they want out,

211
00:11:23,936 --> 00:11:25,440
they'll have to find their own way.

212
00:11:28,060 --> 00:11:36,020
(Handan Pleasure House)

213
00:11:44,780 --> 00:11:46,980
(Mulian Hair Oil)

214
00:12:11,680 --> 00:12:12,840
Why did you bring me here?

215
00:12:12,944 --> 00:12:14,280
I saw a statue of the Virgin Mary

216
00:12:14,280 --> 00:12:15,400
at your house.

217
00:12:15,400 --> 00:12:17,376
I figured your mother
must've been a Christian.

218
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:20,000
I asked around
every church near my home.

219
00:12:20,000 --> 00:12:21,360
No one saw her.

220
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:23,000
That's why I brought you here.

221
00:12:24,160 --> 00:12:25,160
That statue at your house

222
00:12:25,160 --> 00:12:26,600
is a replica of Michelangelo's work.

223
00:12:26,600 --> 00:12:28,520
The originals are all in Italy.

224
00:12:30,304 --> 00:12:31,440
Among the churches in Beijing

225
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,440
run by Italians,

226
00:12:33,584 --> 00:12:34,880
this one's the most well-known.

227
00:12:44,160 --> 00:12:45,160
Madam Yuan.

228
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:48,520
She was deeply devoted to the Lord.

229
00:12:49,040 --> 00:12:50,240
She had a kind heart.

230
00:12:51,080 --> 00:12:53,120
Everyone in the church

231
00:12:53,120 --> 00:12:54,200
liked her very much.

232
00:12:56,760 --> 00:12:58,560
Do you remember

233
00:12:58,560 --> 00:12:59,728
the last time she came here?

234
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:01,280
Last August.

235
00:13:02,000 --> 00:13:03,160
Toward the end of the month.

236
00:13:04,000 --> 00:13:06,240
I heard she passed away not long after.

237
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:08,800
Did anything seem unusual about her?

238
00:13:10,800 --> 00:13:12,240
She looked pale.

239
00:13:12,600 --> 00:13:14,440
It was like she was seriously ill.

240
00:13:15,320 --> 00:13:17,280
Her teeth were loose.
Her hair was falling out.

241
00:13:17,280 --> 00:13:19,520
I heard her bones and joints
were failing,

242
00:13:19,520 --> 00:13:20,800
and so were her kidneys.

243
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,280
She suffered greatly.

244
00:13:24,800 --> 00:13:27,120
Do you know what illness she had?

245
00:13:27,184 --> 00:13:28,440
It didn't seem like an illness.

246
00:13:29,280 --> 00:13:30,600
More like a curse.

247
00:13:31,120 --> 00:13:32,800
I saw several patients

248
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,160
with the same symptoms

249
00:13:34,480 --> 00:13:36,960
when I was in Europe.

250
00:13:37,880 --> 00:13:39,200
Did they recover?

251
00:13:40,200 --> 00:13:41,120
It was incurable.

252
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:42,360
Thought

253
00:13:42,360 --> 00:13:44,840
your mother was taking
a rather unusual tonic.

254
00:13:45,280 --> 00:13:46,240
I believe it was called

255
00:13:46,720 --> 00:13:47,840
Longevity Pill.

256
00:13:48,080 --> 00:13:49,440
Longevity Pill?

257
00:13:52,840 --> 00:13:54,720
Do you know where she got them?

258
00:13:54,720 --> 00:13:56,000
For a while,

259
00:13:56,000 --> 00:13:58,000
many members here were taking them.

260
00:13:58,480 --> 00:14:01,480
They all claimed
they could extend your life.

261
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:03,440
Then they stopped

262
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,520
coming to church.

263
00:14:05,800 --> 00:14:06,800
Did they die?

264
00:14:07,120 --> 00:14:08,200
No.

265
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:09,840
They simply stopped coming.

266
00:14:09,840 --> 00:14:12,560
They said they
no longer believed in God.

267
00:14:12,560 --> 00:14:13,480
When I asked why,

268
00:14:13,480 --> 00:14:14,960
none of them would tell me.

269
00:14:14,960 --> 00:14:15,880
Sadly,

270
00:14:16,560 --> 00:14:18,080
I couldn't bring

271
00:14:18,080 --> 00:14:19,560
those lost sheep back.

272
00:14:21,760 --> 00:14:22,760
Thank you, Father.

273
00:14:28,820 --> 00:14:30,660
(Longevity Pill)

274
00:14:38,160 --> 00:14:39,320
Chief, we found it.

275
00:14:39,632 --> 00:14:41,680
The human trafficking hideout
in Xidan Market

276
00:14:41,680 --> 00:14:43,120
belongs to Jin Bonan.

277
00:14:43,120 --> 00:14:43,760
Before he died,

278
00:14:43,770 --> 00:14:45,488
he had his men stash
two chests of gold bars.

279
00:14:45,552 --> 00:14:48,140
A couple of days ago, they were
delivered to No. 14, Mao'er Alley.

280
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:49,000
Who lives there?

281
00:14:49,000 --> 00:14:49,680
Xu Li.

282
00:14:50,640 --> 00:14:52,040
Secretary Xu at the State Council.

283
00:14:53,480 --> 00:14:54,640
I heard

284
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:56,160
the tram project

285
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,240
is officially under
the Ministry of Transport,

286
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:02,320
but Secretary Xu has been overseeing it.

287
00:15:02,320 --> 00:15:03,728
Once Director Zheng was arrested,

288
00:15:03,744 --> 00:15:05,600
the project was delayed
by at least six months.

289
